item.title: Blog post 1 - Python
item.description: hi =("Hello world, this is my first ever blog post.") # use reticulate to show how R and python can work together: library(reticulate) dogs <- "I have a big dog named Murphy, here is a picture of her sitting in a funny position." print(hi, r.dogs) ## Hello world, this is my first ever blog post. I have a big dog named Murphy, here is a picture of her sitting in a funny position.
